  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ Gas 7</p><p>Chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in half lengthways, then wash thoroughly to remove any grit from between the leaves and slice finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a knob of<strong> butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Add the leek with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook, covered, for 12 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619444693903-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619444693903-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619444693903-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619444693903-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619444693903-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the leek is softening, grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>grated cheese</strong> with the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>–<strong> </strong>these are your <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619444704848-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619444704848-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619444704848-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619444704848-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619444704848-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Separate the <strong>egg yolk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> from the <strong>white<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>by cracking the <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>over a small bowl and catching the yolk in the shell</p><p>Transfer the<strong> yolk</strong> from one shell half to the other several times, until all the whites are in the bowl and you are left with the yolk in the shell</p><p>Set the <strong>egg white</strong> aside for later</p><p>In a separate bowl, combine the <strong>egg yolk</strong> with the<strong> Dijon mustard</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1619444718665-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
